#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:2
msgid "Installation (Ubuntu)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:4
msgid "**Goal:** Install the ``mvsim`` package on Ubuntu and verify it works."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:6
msgid "**Tutorial level:** Advanced"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:8
msgid "**Time:** 10 minutes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:12
msgid "Contents"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:15
msgid "Background"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:17
msgid ""
"`MVSim <https://mvsimulator.readthedocs.io/>`__ (MultiVehicle Simulator) is "
"a lightweight, open-source simulator for mobile robots. It provides 2D "
"physics-based simulation with 3D visualization, supporting differential "
"drive and Ackermann vehicles, multiple sensor types (LiDAR, cameras, IMU, "
"GPS), and native ROS 2 integration via standard message types."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:21
msgid "MVSim is licensed under the BSD 3-clause license."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:24
msgid "Prerequisites"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:26
msgid ""
"It is recommended to understand basic ROS principles covered in the "
"beginner :doc:`../../../../Tutorials`. In particular, :doc:`../../../"
"Beginner-Client-Libraries/Creating-A-Workspace/Creating-A-Workspace` is a "
"useful prerequisite."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:29
msgid ""
"You should have a working ROS 2 installation. Follow the :doc:`ROS 2 install "
"instructions <../../../../Installation>` if needed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:33
msgid "Tasks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:36
msgid "1 Install ``mvsim``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:38
msgid ""
"You can either install the released binary package or build from sources."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:42
msgid "Install from ROS binary packages"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:44
msgid "Run the following command in a terminal:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:46
msgid "$ sudo apt install ros-rolling-mvsim"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:50
msgid "Build from sources"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:52
msgid "Create a ROS 2 workspace if you don't already have one:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:54
msgid "$ mkdir -p ~/ros2_ws/src"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:58
msgid "Source the ROS 2 environment:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:60
msgid "$ source /opt/ros/rolling/setup.bash"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:64
msgid "Clone the MVSim repository:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:66
msgid ""
"$ cd ~/ros2_ws/src\n"
"$ git clone https://github.com/MRPT/mvsim.git --recursive"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:71
msgid "Install dependencies using ``rosdep``:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:73
msgid ""
"$ cd ~/ros2_ws\n"
"$ rosdep install --from-paths src --ignore-src -r -y"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:78
msgid "Build the package:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:80
msgid ""
"$ colcon build --symlink-install --cmake-args -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:84
msgid "Source the workspace:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:86
msgid "$ source install/setup.bash"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:91
msgid "2 Verify the installation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:93
msgid "Check that the ``mvsim`` CLI is available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:95
msgid "$ mvsim --version"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:99
msgid "You should see the installed version number printed to the terminal."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:103
msgid "The ``mvsim`` package provides two executables:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:105
msgid "``mvsim``: the main CLI tool for running the simulator standalone"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:106
msgid ""
"``mvsim_node``: a ROS 2 node wrapper for running the simulator and connect "
"it to other ROS 2 nodes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:109
msgid "3 Launch a demo"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:111
msgid ""
"To quickly verify everything is working, launch the warehouse demo with ROS "
"2:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:113
msgid "$ ros2 launch mvsim demo_warehouse.launch.py"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:117
msgid ""
"You should see the MVSim GUI window open with a Jackal robot in a warehouse "
"environment. Use the keyboard (W/A/S/D keys) to drive the robot."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:121
msgid "Summary"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/Tutorials/Advanced/Simulators/MVSim/Installation-Ubuntu.rst:123
msgid ""
"You have installed MVSim and verified it works by launching a demo world. In "
"the next tutorial, you will learn how to launch different demo scenarios and "
"interact with them through ROS 2 topics."
msgstr ""
